  "time_ut": 1662340003,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbb \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0d86\u0db4\u0dc3\u0dd4 \u0dc4\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0db1\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The egg price gazette will not be reversed",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Naleen Fernando, the Minister of Trade and Food Security, said in a press conference on 04th that the gazette issued setting a control price for the sale of eggs will not be reversed for any reason.",
        "At the press conference held at Minister Naleen Ruwanjiwa Fernando's office in Ja-Ala Dadugama, the minister stated that after several discussions with the egg producers, a control price was set for eggs according to a written document provided by them.",
        "The Minister said that the price of an egg which was sold at a high price of 65 rupees has now become available to the customer at less than 50 rupees and further said that the consumer authority has taken legal action against those who sold eggs at an unfairly high price.",
        "Mr. Naleen Fernando said that he always discussed with the egg producers. The Minister of Trade and Consumer Affairs said here that in the past, chicken producers used rice for human consumption for animal feed, but from now on, steps will be taken to provide corn for animal feed as needed."
      ],
